display="inline"><![CDATA[R^{\circ  n}\in \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>:</fr:p><fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[
 R^{\circ  n} = \underbrace {R\circ \cdots \circ  R}_{n\text { times}}
]]></fr:tex><fr:p>More precisely, we define <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R^{\circ  n}]]></fr:tex> by recursion on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>:</fr:p><fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[
 \begin {aligned}
   R^{\circ  0} &= \mathsf {id}_{A}\\
   R^{\circ {\mathopen {}\left (n+1\right )\mathclose {}}} &= R\circ  R^{\circ  n}
 \end {aligned}
]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
