type="user">jms-00JN</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00JN.xml</fr:route><fr:title
text="Adjacency matrix of a finite directed graph">Adjacency <fr:link
href="jms-00IS.xml"
title="Matrix over a semiring"
addr="jms-00IS"
type="local">matrix</fr:link> of a finite <fr:link
href="jms-00JC.xml"
title="Directed graph"
addr="jms-00JC"
type="local">directed graph</fr:link></fr:title><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>We have seen in <fr:link
href="jms-00I6.xml"
title="Lecture 13: relations and matrices"
addr="jms-00I6"
type="local">Lecture 13</fr:link> (<fr:link
href="jms-00IY.xml"
title="The matrix associated to a finite relation"
addr="jms-00IY"
type="local">Definition <fr:contextual-number
addr="jms-00IY" /></fr:link>) how to turn any relation <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R\colon {\mathopen {}\left  [m\right  ]\mathclose {}}\mathbin {\nrightarrow }{\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> into a <fr:link
href="jms-00IS.xml"
title="Matrix over a semiring"
addr="jms-00IS"
type="local">matrix</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}R\in \mathrm {Mat}_{\mathbb {B}}{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> over the boolean semiring. When <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R\in \mathrm {Rel}{\mathopen {}\left ({\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is the <fr:em>edge relation</fr:em> in a graph with vertices in the finite set <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, we refer to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}R\in \mathrm {Mat}_{\mathbb {B}}{\mathopen {}\left (n,n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> as the <fr:em><fr:strong>adjacency matrix</fr:strong></fr:em> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
title="Jon Sterling"
addr="jonmsterling"
type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author><fr:contributor><fr:link
href="marcelofiore.xml"
title="Marcelo Fiore"
addr="marcelofiore"
type="local">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>21</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>7657</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="user">jms-00JV</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00JV.xml</fr:route><fr:title
text="The adjacency matrix of the reflexive-transitive closure">The <fr:link
href="jms-00JN.xml"
title="Adjacency matrix of a finite directed graph"
addr="jms-00JN"
type="local">adjacency matrix</fr:link> of the <fr:link
href="jms-00JH.xml"
title="The reflexive-transitive closure of an endo-relation"
addr="jms-00JH"
type="local">reflexive-transitive closure</fr:link></fr:title><fr:taxon>Algorithm</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M = \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}R]]></fr:tex> be the <fr:link
href="jms-00JN.xml"
title="Adjacency matrix of a finite directed graph"
addr="jms-00JN"
type="local">adjacency matrix</fr:link> of a  finite <fr:link
href="jms-00JC.xml"
title="Directed graph"
addr="jms-00JC"
type="local">directed graph</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left ({\mathopen {}\left  [n\right  ]\mathclose {}},R\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. We will show that the <fr:link
href="jms-00JN.xml"
title="Adjacency matrix of a finite directed graph"
addr="jms-00JN"
type="local">adjacency matrix</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M^*]]></fr:tex> of the <fr:link
href="jms-00JH.xml"
title="The reflexive-transitive closure of an endo-relation"
addr="jms-00JH"
type="local">reflexive-transitive closure</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R^{\circ *}]]></fr:tex> can be computed recursively using the <fr:link
href="jms-00JS.xml"
title="Adding matrices together"
addr="jms-00JS"
type="local">additive</fr:link> and <fr:link
href="jms-00IW.xml"
title="Multiplication of matrices"
addr="jms-00IW"
type="local">multiplicative</fr:link> structure of <fr:link
href="jms-00IS.xml"
title="Matrix over a semiring"
addr="jms-00IS"
type="local">matrices</fr:link>. In particular, we can define <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M^* = M_n]]></fr:tex> where <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M_k]]></fr:tex> is computed recursively as below:</fr:p><fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[
 \begin {aligned}
   M_0 &= I^n\\
   M_{k+1} &= I^n + {\mathopen {}\left (M\cdot  M_k\right )\mathclose {}}
 \end {aligned}
]]></fr:tex><fr:p>Thus we have a recursive algorithm that can deicde whether there is a path between two elemetns in a finite <fr:link
href="jms-00JC.xml"
title="Directed graph"
addr="jms-00JC"
type="local">directed graph</fr:link>: indeed, there is a path from <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[t]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> if and only if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M^*_{s,t} =\mathsf {true}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree
show-metadata="false"
toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
title="Jon Sterling"
addr="jonmsterling"
type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>21</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>7656</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="machine">unstable/875</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-875.xml</fr:route><fr:title
text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>We first unravel the first few <html:span
style="white-space: nowrap"
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M_k]]></fr:tex>’s</html:span> to get a better understanding.</fr:p>

 <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[
  \begin {aligned}
   M_1 &= I^n + M\cdot  M_0
   \\
   &= I^n+M\cdot  I^n
   \\
   &= I^n + M
   \\
   M_2 &= I^n + M\cdot  M_1
   \\
   &= I^n + M\cdot  (I^n + M)
   \\
   &= I^n + M\cdot  I^n + M\cdot  M
   \\
   &= I^n + M + M^2
  \end {aligned}
 ]]></fr:tex>

 <fr:p>By induction, we can extend the pattern above to a closed form for each <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M_k]]></fr:tex>. In particular, we deduce that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M_k = \sum _{l\leq  k} M^l]]></fr:tex> by recalling from <fr:link
href="jms-00J3.xml"
title="Associativity and unit laws of matrix products"
addr="jms-00J3"
type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number
addr="jms-00J3" /></fr:link> that the <fr:link
href="jms-00IT.xml"
title="The identity matrix"
addr="jms-00IT"
type="local">identity matrix</fr:link> is the neutral element for <fr:link
href="jms-00IV.xml"
title="Product of matrices"
addr="jms-00IV"
type="local">matrix multiplication</fr:link>. Therefore, we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M_n =\sum _{k \leq  n}M^k]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>

 <fr:p>Our goal is to show that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M_n = \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}} R^{\circ  *}]]></fr:tex>; we have already seen in <fr:link
href="jms-00JR.xml"
title="Matrix addition and union of relations"
addr="jms-00JR"
type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number
addr="jms-00JR" /></fr:link> and <fr:link
href="jms-00J2.xml"
title="Matrix product is relational composition"
addr="jms-00J2"
type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number
addr="jms-00J2" /></fr:link> that <fr:link
href="jms-00JO.xml"
title="Pointwise addition of matrices"
addr="jms-00JO"
type="local">matrix addition</fr:link> corresponds to union of <fr:link
href="jms-00I7.xml"
title="Relation"
addr="jms-00I7"
type="local">relations</fr:link> and <fr:link
href="jms-00IV.xml"
title="Product of matrices"
addr="jms-00IV"
type="local">matrix multiplication</fr:link> corresponds to <fr:link
href="jms-00IN.xml"
title="Relational composite"
addr="jms-00IN"
type="local">relational composition</fr:link>.</fr:p>

 <fr:p>By <fr:link
href="jms-00JU.xml"
title="Reflexive-transitive closure of finite endo-relations"
addr="jms-00JU"
type="local">Observation <fr:contextual-number
addr="jms-00JU" /></fr:link> (<fr:link
href="jms-00JU.xml"
title="Reflexive-transitive closure of finite endo-relations"
addr="jms-00JU"
type="local">reflexive-transitive closure of <fr:em>finite</fr:em> <fr:link
href="jms-00JF.xml"
title="Path in a directed graph"
addr="jms-00JF"
type="local">endo-relations</fr:link></fr:link>), we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R^{\circ *} = \bigcup _{k\leq  n} R^{\circ  k}]]></fr:tex>. Therefore:</fr:p>

 <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[
  \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}R^{\circ *} = \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}\bigcup _{k\leq  n} R^{\circ  k}
 ]]></fr:tex>

 <fr:p>By <fr:link
href="jms-00JR.xml"
title="Matrix addition and union of relations"
addr="jms-00JR"
type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number
addr="jms-00JR" /></fr:link> (<fr:link
href="jms-00JR.xml"
title="Matrix addition and union of relations"
addr="jms-00JR"
type="local"><fr:link
href="jms-00JO.xml"
title="Pointwise addition of matrices"
addr="jms-00JO"
type="local">matrix addition</fr:link> and union of <fr:link
href="jms-00I7.xml"
title="Relation"
addr="jms-00I7"
type="local">relations</fr:link></fr:link>), we have:</fr:p>

 <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[
  \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}\bigcup _{k\leq  n} R^{\circ  k}
  =
  \sum _{k\leq  n} \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}R^{\circ  k}
 ]]></fr:tex>

 By <fr:link
href="jms-00J2.xml"
title="Matrix product is relational composition"
addr="jms-00J2"
type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number
addr="jms-00J2" /></fr:link> (<fr:link
href="jms-00J2.xml"
title="Matrix product is relational composition"
addr="jms-00J2"
type="local"><fr:link
href="jms-00IV.xml"
title="Product of matrices"
addr="jms-00IV"
type="local">matrix product</fr:link> is <fr:link
href="jms-00IN.xml"
title="Relational composite"
addr="jms-00IN"
type="local">relational composition</fr:link></fr:link>), we have:
 <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[
  \sum _{k\leq  n} \operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}R^{\circ  k}  =
  \sum _{k\leq  n} {\mathopen {}\left (\operatorname {\underline {mat}}_{\mathbb {B}}R\right )\mathclose {}}^k
  =
  \sum _{k\leq  n} M^k
  = M_n
 ]]></fr:tex>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
