text="Path in a directed graph">Path in a directed graph</fr:title><fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (A,R\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link
href="jms-00JC.xml"
title="Directed graph"
addr="jms-00JC"
type="local">directed graph</fr:link>. For <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s,t\in  A]]></fr:tex>, a <fr:em><fr:strong>path</fr:strong></fr:em> of length <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n\in  \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> with <fr:em><fr:strong>source</fr:strong></fr:em> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[s]]></fr:tex> and <fr:em><fr:strong>target</fr:strong></fr:em> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[t]]></fr:tex> is a tuple <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (a_0,\ldots ,a_n\right )\mathclose {}}\in  A^{n+1}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a_0=s]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a_n=t]]></fr:tex>, and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a_i\mathrel {R}a_{i+1}]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[0\leq  i <n]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
